# “Other” TypeScript templates (from `other.json`)

Summarizes **`.ts`** (and a few **`.js`**) utility and service files. Typical content: **`src/lib/`**, **`src/features/`** services, **`.agents/scripts`**.

## Inventory snapshot

| Fact | Typical value |
| --- | --- |
| Extensions | `.ts` (~92%), `.js`, `.mjs`, `.cjs` |
| Path depth (median) | 5 segments |
| Top roots | `app/utils` (~32%), `app/pages` (~31%), `app/features` (~18%), `.agents/tools/rag` (~4%), `app/services` (~4%) |

## Buckets

| Area | Examples |
| --- | --- |
| Pure utilities | `app/utils/**` — functions, small modules, **`camelCase`** file names (**`@utility-naming-conventions.mdc`**) |
| Loaders / actions | `app/pages/**` route data loading, form actions |
| Services | `app/features/**/services/**`, `app/services/**` |
| Rx subjects | `app/subjects/**` |
| Tooling | `.agents/tools/rag/**`, `.agents/scripts/**` |

## Template — pure function module

```typescript
const add = (a: number, b: number): number => a + b;

export default add;
```

## Template — named exports

```typescript
export const toUpper = (value: string): string => value.toUpperCase();

export const toLower = (value: string): string => value.toLowerCase();
```

## Boundaries

- If a file **starts using React hooks**, move it to **`hooks/`** and name with **`use`**.
- If it is **only types**, use **`types/`** or **`*.type.ts`** so it lands in **`types.json`**, not **`other.json`**, next time lists are generated.

## Related

- **`@existing-utilities.mdc`** (reuse before adding)
- **`hooks-templates.mdc`**, **`types-templates.mdc`**
